At least for this (current) semester, there was form that goes out later that lets you sign up to take the class -- priority is, of course, given to people who *NEED* to take the class. So (presumably), just wait for that form to come out later.

------

There's no reason to enroll in the course until you know you're going to become a TA. The assignments for the course assume that you are a TA (e.g. writing reflections / video-taping your own discussion sections), and the class is not meant for people who simply intend to be a TA.

At least for this (current) semester, there was form that goes out later that lets you sign up to take the class -- priority is, of course, given to people who *NEED* to take the class. So (presumably), just wait for that form to come out later.

Instructions will be sent in your offer email, but we will do a google form again for UGSIs since the system won't let you enroll in graduate courses on your own.

Graduate students have first priority for EE 375, which is why we'll begin enrolling UGSIs later, most likely in August.

I'm planning on becoming a TA either next semester or the one after, and I want to enroll in 375 now. However, when I try to, it says:

Error: Permission to enroll in this class is required. The class falls outside your career of study. Choose another class.

I would assume that EECS should be eligible.. I saw some posts from last semester saying that I should e-mail the professor, but as of now, there is no instructor assigned yet either.

Is there anything I can do?
